Let $(X,T)$ be a topological dynamical system. We define the
measure-theoretical lower and upper entropies $\underline{h}_\mu(T)$,
$\bar{h}_\mu(T)$ for any $\mu\in M(X)$, where $M(X)$ denotes the collection of
all Borel probability measures on $X$. For any non-empty compact subset $K$ of
$X$, we show that $$\htop^B(T, K)= \sup \{\underline{h}_\mu(T): \mu\in M(X),\;
\mu(K)=1\}, $$ $$\htop^P(T, K)= \sup \{\bar{h}_\mu(T): \mu\in M(X),\;
\mu(K)=1\}. $$ where $\htop^B(T, K)$ denotes Bowen's topological entropy of
$K$, and $\htop^P(T, K)$ the packing topological entropy of $K$. Furthermore,
when $\htop(T)<\infty$, the first equality remains valid when $K$ is replaced
by an arbitrarily analytic subset of $X$. The second equality always extends to
any analytic subset of $X$.